cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the security aspects of OAuth 2.0 and OpenID Connect, which are related to cryptography and network security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). However, since the paper also discusses the interactions between different roles and the establishment of trust, it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, since the protocols involve network communication, it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
